com.mumfrey.liteloader.api

Interface Observer

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    CoreProvider, EnumerationObserver, GenericObserver<T>, InterfaceObserver, ModLoadObserver, PanelManager<TParentScreen>, PostRenderObserver, ShutdownObserver, TickObserver, WorldObserver
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Input, InputManager, LiteLoaderCoreProviderClient, LiteLoaderEventBroker, LiteLoaderEventBrokerClient, LiteLoaderPanelManager, ModEvents, ResourceObserver

    public interface Observer
    LiteLoader Extensible API - Observer base interface

    Observers are essentially "core listeners" which are objects which make up the core a of a particular API implementation and sink events generated by the Loader or by other observable components. See the derived interfaces for more detail.

    Author:
    Adam Mummery-Smith
